            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "དཔལ་མགོན་པོ་ནག་པོ་ནག་པོའི་རྒྱུད་ལས་རྟགས་ཀྱི་རིམ་པའི་ལེའུ་སྟེ་དྲུག་པའོ།། །།",
            "english": "This is chapter 6 in “The Tantra of Glorious Mahākāla” on “A Series of Signs of Accomplishment.” Chapter 7: Hailstorms",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-136",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "དེ་ནས་ཡང་དག་བཤད་བྱ་བ། །སེར་བ་དབབ་པའི་ལས་བྱ་ན། །",
            "english": "“Next, I will teach the following: To perform a rite to make it hail,",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-137",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "མོན་ནམ་མཛེ་ཅན་ཐོད་པ་རུ། །འཁོར་ལོ་རྩིབས་བཞི་བྲིས་ནས་ཀྱང་། །རིགས་ལྔ་ཀླུ་ཡི་ས་བོན་དགོད། །",
            "english": "Draw a wheel with four spokes In the skull of a tribal person or a leper. “Inscribe it with the seed syllables of the five classes of nāgas.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-138",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "རྩིབས་ཆེན་སེར་སྲུང་མིང་རུས་དང་། །ཡུལ་དུ་ཕོབ་ཅིས་བྱ་བ་བྲིས། །",
            "english": "The large spokes should bear the name and family names of the hail protectors And have the phrase ‘fall in this country’ written on them.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-138",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "དེ་མཐར་འཁོར་ལོ་རྩིབས་དགུ་ལ། །དྲེགས་པའི་སྔགས་དག་བྲི་བར་བྱ། །",
            "english": "Write the mantras of the arrogant spirit beings “On a wheel with nine spokes outside of that.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-139",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "རྒྱབ་ཏུ་གང་ཡིན་ཡུལ་མིང་དང་། །རླུང་གི་སྙིང་པོ་བྲི་བར་བྱ། །",
            "english": "Write the name of the country and The wind heart mantra on the back side.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-139",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "བདག་ཉིད་པདྨ་ཁྲོས་པར་བསྒོམ། །",
            "english": "Visualize yourself as Wrathful Lotus",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-139",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "གསང་སྔགས་འདི་ཡིས་གནད་ལ་བོར། །",
            "english": "“And strike their vital points using this mantra:",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-140",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "ཨོཾ་བཛྲ་མ་ཧཱ་ཀཱ་ལ་ཀྵིཾ་ཀྵེ་ཏྲ་བིགྷྣཱྃ་བི་ནཱ་ཡ་ཀ་ཧཱུྃ་ཧཱུྃ་ཕཊ། ནཱ་ག་སྙིང་གཟིར།",
            "english": "oṃ vajramahākāla kṣiṃ kṣetravighnān vināyaka hūṁ hūṁ phaṭ | torment the nāga’s mind | phu create obstacles ja khroṃ śar hril bhyo | “Recite that mantra while",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-142",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "ཕུ་ཧུར་ཐུམ་ཛ་ཁྲོ་ཤར་ཧྲིལ་བྷྱོ། །དེ་སྐད་ཅེས་ནི་རབ་བརྗོད་ལ། །ཡུངས་ཀར་ཡུངས་ནག་སྐེ་ཚེ་དང་། །ཁྲག་དང་དུག་གིས་ཐོད་པར་བྲབ། །ལོ་འབྲས་རླུང་ཁྱེར་རྟགས་བྱུང་ན",
            "english": "Pelting the skull with white and black Mustard seeds, blood, and poison. “If a gust of wind carries off the harvest, it is a sign",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-145",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "དགྲ་ཡི་ཡུལ་དུ་དབབ་པར་བྱ། །",
            "english": "That hail will fall in the enemy’s country.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-145",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.a",
            "tibetan": "གལ་ཏེ་འཇིག་རྟེན་ཕུང་བའོ། །",
            "english": "If it does, it will bring ruin to the people.”",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-145",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/401"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.b",
            "tibetan": "དཔལ་མགོན་པོ་ནག་པོའི་རྒྱུད་ལས་སེར་བ་དབབ་པའི་ལེའུ་སྟེ་བདུན་པའོ།། །།",
            "english": "This is chapter 7 in “The Tantra of Glorious Mahākāla” on “Hailstorms.” Chapter 8",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-146",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/402"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.b",
            "tibetan": "དེ་ནས་ཡང་དག་ངེས་གསུངས་པ། །ཨེ་མ་འཁོར་འདུས་ངོ་མཚར་ཅན། །མ་འོངས་དམ་ཅན་སྒྲུབ་བྱེད་ན། །",
            "english": "Then he gave the following definitive instruction: “Marvelous ones gathered in this assembly, In the future, when samaya holders perform this sādhana,",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-149",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/402"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.b",
            "tibetan": "དམ་ཚིག་ལ་གནས་སྡོམ་པ་གཟུང་། །",
            "english": "They should maintain the samayas, uphold the vows, “And diligently perform the bali offerings.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-150",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/402"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.b",
            "tibetan": "གཏོར་མ་དག་ལ་བརྩོན་པར་བྱ། །",
            "english": "They should wear the samaya substances and soul stones on their body.”",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-150",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/402"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.b",
            "tibetan": "དམ་རྫས་བླ་རྡོ་ལུས་ལ་བསྲེལ། །ཞེས་གསུངས་པས་རྒྱལ་པོ་མིག་མི་བཟང་ལ་སོགས་པའི་འཁོར་རྣམས་ཡི་རངས་ནས། ནག་པོ་ཆེན་པོས་བསྟན་པ་སྲུང་བར་ཁས་བླངས་ནས་མི་སྣང་བར་གྱུར་ཏོ། །",
            "english": "After he said that, King Virūpakṣa along with the rest of the assembly rejoiced, promised to maintain Mahākāla’s teaching, and then vanished.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-151",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/402"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.b",
            "tibetan": "དཔལ་ནག་པོ་ཆེན་པོའི་རྒྱུད་ལས་ལེའུ་བརྒྱད་པ་རྫོགས་སོ།། །།",
            "english": "This concludes chapter 8 in “The Tantra of Glorious Mahākāla.”",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-152",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "91",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9217-0000/side/402"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.201.b",
            "tibetan": "།​།རྒྱ་གར་གྱི་མཁན་པོ་ཨ་མོ་གྷ་བཛྲ་དང་། བོད་ཀྱི་ལོ་ཙྪ་བ་ཕུར་བུ་འོད་ཀྱིས་བསྒྱུར་བའོ།​།",
            "english": "This text was translated by the Indian preceptor Amoghavajra and the Tibetan translator Phurbu Ö.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-091-064-153",
